Overview

This project implements a movie recommendation system using two matrix factorization techniques:

Scenario 1: Singular Value Decomposition (SVD)
Scenario 2: Non-negative Matrix Factorization (NMF)

The system uses the MovieLens 100K dataset to predict user ratings for unseen movies and recommend top movies based on user preferences.

Dataset

Dataset Used: MovieLens 100K
Source: Kaggle
Link: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/abhikjha/movielens-100k

Features:
User ID
Movie ID
Rating
Target:
Predict ratings for unseen movies
Scenario 1: Matrix Factorization using SVD
Objective

To decompose the user-item rating matrix into latent factors and predict missing ratings.

Steps Performed
Imported required libraries:
NumPy
Pandas
Matplotlib
Seaborn
Scikit-learn
SciPy
Loaded MovieLens dataset
Performed preprocessing:
Checked missing values
Converted data into pivot table
Created User-Item Interaction Matrix
Applied Mean Centering (Normalization)
Applied Singular Value Decomposition (SVD)
Selected optimal latent factors (k)
Reconstructed rating matrix
Predicted missing ratings
Generated Top-N movie recommendations
Evaluation Metrics
RMSE (Root Mean Square Error)
MAE (Mean Absolute Error)
Analysis
Studied impact of different latent factors (k)
Compared actual and predicted ratings
Observed dimensionality reduction benefits
Checked overfitting and underfitting behavior
Visualizations
Heatmap of original user-item matrix
Heatmap of reconstructed matrix
Error vs latent factors graph
Top recommended movies chart
Scenario 2: Matrix Factorization using NMF
Objective

To use Non-negative Matrix Factorization for discovering hidden user-item preference patterns.

Steps Performed
Loaded dataset
Created user-item matrix
Handled missing values:
Filled with 0 / mean values
Applied NMF model
Factorized matrix into:
User-feature matrix
Item-feature matrix
Reconstructed matrix
Predicted ratings
Generated Top-N recommendations
Evaluation Metrics
RMSE
Precision@K
Recall@K
Analysis
Compared recommendation accuracy with SVD
Observed interpretability of NMF factors
Analyzed sparse matrix handling
Compared diversity in recommendations
Visualizations
Latent feature matrix plots
Original vs reconstructed matrix comparison
Top movie recommendation rankings
